messages.message:
Hi Anil,

Sorry, I’ll be off for the next two days. Quick update for last week:

	1.	*Results API Changes* - Need to implement; Hannah confirmed the changes.
	2.	*License Bug* - Can you review the PR? PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/66025)
	3.	*Job Table Migration* -
	     •	*Done*: Migration, migration tests, accessor, main code changes for writes and updates, and testing.
	     • *Pending*: Need to modify reads.
	4.	*Fix List Jobs Query* - thread (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CV8V33RPV/p1733867311590289) PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/66181)
	     •	Issue: For AXA, there’s an upstream Azure system that sets the job-id as a mixed-case string, but our job-id DB query converts the query to lowercase, causing results not to appear.
	     •	Fixed in PR, but the PR was held up because Andy and Matt suggested implementing case-insensitive search.
	     •	Worked with Matt to implement for case-insensitive search, but Kerry suggested not merging the PR since other customers might rely on the current search behavior.
	5.	*New Issue* - Spent time debugging but couldn’t root cause yet: FLOW-10515 (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/FLOW-10515).
	6.	**ACTION ITEM*** *Update Jira*  - Docs team (@Chris Cowell) reached out regarding updates on two tickets EPD- 3194 (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-3194), EPD-3110 (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-3110?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiZDI5ZTY4OGY4MTA5NDIyMGEwN2E4Yjk0NGI3NTZkNjMiLCJwIjoiamlyYS1zbGFjay1pbnQifQ). Since these are not complete and need to be pushed, he asked to add a note explaining the delay and for the version label to be updated. I’m unsure what reason to provide—can you please update it?

I’ll be online, please let me know if I should do anything. Thanks again Anil.

Can you also move our 1:1 from Monday to Wednesday ?
